00038 class   uoqueue {
00039 public:
00040   inline uoqueue(void){q_len = 0;}
00041   inline ~uoqueue() {}
00042   inline void enqueue(root *obj)
00043   {     
00044     if (q_len++ == 0)
00045       q_head.next = q_last = obj;
00046     else {
00047       q_last->next = obj;
00048       q_last = obj;
00049     }
00050   }
00051   inline void enqHead(root *obj)
00052   {
00053     if (q_len++ == 0)
00054       q_head.next = q_last = obj;
00055     else {
00056       obj->next = q_head.next;
00057       q_head.next = obj;
00058     }
00059   }
00060   inline        void    enqTime(root *obj)
00061   {
00062     root        *p;
00063     // do not inc q_len until call of findPrecTime() !
00064     if ((p = findPrecTime(obj->time)) == NULL)
00065       // queue empty or new largest time.
00066       // See remark three lines above.
00067       enqueue(obj);
00068     else {
00069       // it is sure: p can't be the last item
00070       obj->next = p->next;
00071       p->next = obj;
00072       ++q_len;
00073     }
00074   }
00075 
00076   inline int enqPrec(root *obj, root *ref)
00077   {     
00078     root *p;
00079     if ((p = findPrec(ref)) == NULL)
00080       return FALSE;
00081     ++q_len;
00082     // sure: p can't be the last item (ref follows)
00083     p->next = obj;
00084     obj->next = ref;
00085     return TRUE;
00086   }
00087 
00088   inline int enqSuc(root *obj, root *ref)
00089   {     
00090     if (isQueued(ref) == FALSE)
00091       return FALSE;
00092     // q_len must be at least 1 (since ref was found)
00093     ++q_len;
00094     if (ref == q_last)
00095       { // ref was the last, add at tail
00096         q_last->next = obj;
00097         q_last = obj;
00098       }
00099     else {
00100       // include after ref
00101       obj->next = ref->next;
00102       ref->next = obj;
00103     }
00104     return TRUE;
00105   }

00107   inline root *dequeue(void)
00108   {
00109     if (q_len-- == 0)
00110       { q_len = 0;
00111       return NULL;
00112       }
00113     root        *obj = q_head.next;
00114     q_head.next = obj->next;
00115     return obj;
00116   }

00120   inline root *deqTime(tim_typ tim)
00121   {     
00122     root *p, *p2;
00123     if ((p = findPrecTime(tim)) == NULL)
00124       return NULL;

00151     int i;

00202   //    These methods return the pointer to q_head if the desired

00204   inline        root    *findPrec(root *obj)
00205   {
00206     int i;
00207     root *p = &q_head;
00208     for (i = 0; i < q_len; ++i){

00217   {
00218     int i;
00219     root        *p = &q_head;
00220     for (i = 0; i < q_len; ++i){        
00221       if (p->next->time >= tim)
00222         return p;
00223       else
